      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Bad",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There’s no point beating around the bush. As we often find in games released on multiple platforms these days, the Nintendo Switch version is often squeezed and optimised to breaking point. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Hell Pie",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is no exception. At the time of writing this review, my save file is unplayable because I got to a particular sub-level (more on those later) and the game crashed. Now when I restart my save file, I restart in the same area and the game just crashes after  2 or 3 seconds each time. This is hugely disappointing as I was really enjoying ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Hell Pie",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " up to this point.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Regarding those sub-levels, they’re basically smaller levels within each world where you have to get from A to B to obtain a collectible, and they are considerably more mundane and frustrating than the main worlds. Each time I came across one, my heart sank as it broke up the fun and expansive exploration that the rest of the game brings to the table.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Lastly, much of the environment art felt quite rushed. There are plenty of gaps between textures which could either be because of the Switch optimisation or because the game was rushed out of the door… Or perhaps a little from column A and a little from column B!",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
